lina State Board of Elections]].<ref name=\":1\" /> On February 25, 2019, the board announced in an online press release that its five members had unanimously agreed to hold a special election.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ncsbe.gov/Press-Releases?udt_2226_param_detail=229|title=State Board unanimously orders new election in 9th Congressional District|author=[[North Carolina State Board of Elections]]|website=ncsbe.gov|date=2019-02-25|access-date=2020-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811143151/https://www.ncsbe.gov/Press-Releases?udt_2226_param_detail=229|archive-date=2019-08-11}}</ref> The [[2019 North Carolina's 9th congressional district special election]] was held as a result.<ref>[https://www.charlotteobserver.com/news/politics-government/article226864674.html Bladen County operative at center of NC election fraud investigation indicted, arrested], ''[[Charlotte Observer]]'', Ely Portillo and Jim Morrill, February 27, 2019. Retrieved April 7, 2019.</ref>\n\nVote harvesting is illegal in Texas, where state law mandates that absentee ballots cannot be sent by a person on another's behalf.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.pleasantonexpress.com/articles/how-to-prevent-vote-harvesting/|title=How to prevent vote harvesting|date=2019-04-25|website=pleasantonexpress.com|first=Tom|last=Firme|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190604033125/https://www.pleasantonexpress.com/articles/how-to-prevent-vote-harvesting/|archive-date=2019-06-04}}</ref> In 2013, a state bill was passed, aiming to prevent ballot harvesting by making it a misdemeanor to give or receive compensation for collecting mail-in ballots in any election.<ref>{{Cite news|title=New Voting Law Aims to Curb Ballot Harvesting|url=https://www.texastribune.org/2013/08/22/31-days-31-ways-laws-mail-ballots-takes-effect/|website=texastribune.org|last1=Aguilar|first1=Juli\u00e1n|last2=Wiseman|first2=Todd|date=2013-08-22|access-date=2020-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web